<abstract>
<p>Over 50 years have elapsed since the first experimental observations of dynamic edge phenomena on elastic structures, yet the topic remains a diverse and vibrant source of research activity. This article provides a focused history and overview of such phenomena with a particular emphasis on structures such as strips, rods, plates and shells. Within this context, some of the recent research highlights are discussed and the contents of this special issue of <italic>Mathematics and Mechanics of Solids</italic> on dynamical edge phenomena are introduced.</p>
</abstract>
